<br>
The greatest error that can be made in prosecuting a war is to fail to respect your enemy!<br>
<br>
If you do not respect your enemy, he <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">will</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> outwit you and, at best, Victory will be denied to you, at worst you will be defeated!<br>
<br>
The greatest military humiliations come from making this grave error.<br>
<br>
The Nazis failed to respect the Russians in WWII (They called them “Untermench” or Subhuman) and they lost!<br>
<br>
The British failed to respect the Turks in WWI and suffered a series of devastating defeats, including one at Kut, close to where we are fighting now! A point, I’m sure, not lost on “Saladin” BTW!<br>
<br>
*Both* the British and the US lacked respect for the Japanese in WWII and we both got seriously hurt by them. It should be pointed out that we didn’t defeat the Japanese in WWII; they surrendered, not after a crushing battle, but after an overwhelming demonstration of technical superiority! We made them an offer they couldn’t refuse! It is interesting to consider what may have happened if they had called our bluff? We only ever had three bombs and by then we had used them all,! (How long it would have taken to make more I don’t know)<br>
<br>
More recently The US has suffered defeats (and tragedy) in Somalia by failing to respect the enemy.<br>
<br>
Do I hate Sadham? Not really, I don’t know him well enough!<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Do I think he is an evil bastard? Most certainly!<br>
<br>
Do I respect and even secretly admire him? Oh Yes!!!<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :satansmoke --><img src=http://www.smilies-world.de/Smilies/Smilies_klein_1/sasmokin.gif ALT=":satansmoke"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
He may be an evil bastard, without whom, the world would be a much better place, but he is a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Cunning</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> evil bastard who has run circles round us for the last 12 years and he is still doing so now. I am <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>amazed</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> at his ability to pull Victory (IE Survival) from the jaws of defeat time after time!<br>
<br>
I just wonder what sort of rabbit he’s going to pull out of the hat this time?<br>
<br>
I think the British Army in Basra are showing due respect to both the civilian and the military population (Both in helping them and fighting them!<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :jedi --><img src=http://www.smilies-world.de/Smilies/Smilies_boese_1/lsabre.gif ALT=":jedi"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) and we seem to be making steady progress there, both militarily and with the “Hearts and minds” bit. However I am not so sure about US forces further north (Saddam’s the disease, we’re the chemotherapy, Oh come on!<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :purpleunhappy --><img src=http://www.smilies-world.de/Smilies/Smilies_klein_1/Smilies_klein_1_1/shakemitkopf.gif ALT=":purpleunhappy"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). <br>
<br>
The idea that the Iraqi forces would turn to jelly at the first bark of US High technology is based, primarily, on a lack of respect! If you don’t learn to respect them and their leadership, you wont be able to defeat them! Ever!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Dusty<br>
